Females show size-dependent dimorphism in the colour pattern of the hair: large queens vary from having T2 black with a few yellow hairs (in the east) to having T2 predominantly yellow (in the far west in 
Pakistan
) and T4 is white; whereas the smaller workers have T2 extensively yellow and T4 red. Males have a similar colour pattern to the workers. That the castes and sexes are conspecific has been confirmed from examining variation within one colony from Kashmir (
Williams 1991
).
